    • Method Detail

      • asDataArray

        <Q> Q[] asDataArray(Q[] a)
        Get the feature-vector data of the list as a two-dimensional array of data. The number of rows will equal the number of features in the list, and the type must be compatible with the data type of the features themselves.
        Type Parameters:
        Q - the data type
        Parameters:
        a - the array to fill
        Returns:
        the array, filled with the feature-vector data.

      • vecLength

        int vecLength()
        Get the length of the feature-vectors of each local feature if they are constant. This value is used as instantiate new local features in the case that the local feature has a constructor that takes a single integer.
        Returns:
        the feature-vector length
